<TITLE> Khaleda holds BNP policy meet </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 14 (bdnews24.com) - BNP chairperson and leader of the opposition Khaleda Zia resumed a meeting of the party's standing committee on Saturday, on the "overall political situation of the country". The meeting, which was adjourned last week, was held at the chairperson's Gulshan office from 7.30pm, said BNP's office secretary Rizvi Ahmed. "The overall political condition of the country was reviewed at the meeting, presided over by Khaleda Zia, resuming from the meeting that was adjourned on February 10 last, " Rizvi Ahmed told bdnews24.com. Khaleda convened an 'urgent meeting' of the party's top policy making forum last Tuesday. The meeting had discussed the political situation of the country and international issues, including the visit of Indian external affairs minister and the issue of Indian transit, said BNP leaders after last Tuesday's meeting. The members of the standing committee beside the BNP chairperson are: M Saifur Rahman, Khandakar Delwar Hossain, Khondakar Mosharraf Hossain, Abdul Matin Chowdhury, R. A Gani, Chowdhury Tanvir Ahmed Siddiqui, Moudud Ahmed, Khondakar Mahbubuddin Ahmed, Lt Gen (retd) Mahbubur Rahman and M Shamsul Islam. bdnew
